	"content": "<h1 class=\"page-title\">Intro to Python for Finance (Optional)</h1>\n  \n  <div id=\"todo-date-mount-point\"></div>\n  \n    <p>If you are interested in learning Python as used in Finance, here are some materials to get you started. This is completely optional (no impact on your class grade), so feel free to disregard if you are not interested.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Python is the language of machine learning models that have become increasingly popular in the last few years. These include artificial intelligence models such as those developed by Open AI (Chat GPT) and Google (Gemini). These models are also beginning to&nbsp; make inroads into finance as well.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Below are some materials to get you started on your journey to apply Python in finance.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Set Up</span></p>\n<p>We will use Google's Colab environment that was designed specifically for Python projects. All Python projects are coded in Jupyter notebooks. To get on Google's Colab, simply go to: <a class=\"inline_disabled external\" href=\"http://colab.google\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><span>colab.google</span><span class=\"external_link_icon\" style=\"margin-inline-start: 5px; display: inline-block; text-indent: initial; \" role=\"presentation\"><svg viewBox=\"0 0 1920 1920\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" style=\"width:1em; height:1em; vertical-align:middle; fill:currentColor\">\n    <path d=\"M1226.667 267c88.213 0 160 71.787 160 160v426.667H1280v-160H106.667v800C106.667 1523 130.56 1547 160 1547h1066.667c29.44 0 53.333-24 53.333-53.333v-213.334h106.667v213.334c0 88.213-71.787 160-160 160H160c-88.213 0-160-71.787-160-160V427c0-88.213 71.787-160 160-160Zm357.706 442.293 320 320c20.8 20.8 20.8 54.614 0 75.414l-320 320-75.413-75.414 228.907-228.906H906.613V1013.72h831.254L1508.96 784.707l75.413-75.414Zm-357.706-335.626H160c-29.44 0-53.333 24-53.333 53.333v160H1280V427c0-29.333-23.893-53.333-53.333-53.333Z\" fill-rule=\"evenodd\"></path>\n</svg>\n<span class=\"screenreader-only\">Links to an external site.</span></span></a> and click on Open Colab.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Samples of Jupyter Notebooks</span></p>\n<p>To get started here are two Jupyter Notebooks that you can load into Colab:</p>\n<p><span class=\"instructure_file_holder link_holder instructure_file_link_holder\"><a class=\"inline_disabled\" title=\"Notebook_Sample_1.ipynb\" href=\"https://canvas.colorado.edu/courses/123249/files/81499492?wrap=1\" target=\"_blank\" data-canvas-previewable=\"false\" data-api-endpoint=\"https://canvas.colorado.edu/api/v1/courses/123249/files/81499492\" data-api-returntype=\"File\">Notebook_Sample_1.ipynb</a><a class=\"file_download_btn\" role=\"button\" download=\"\" style=\"margin-inline-start: 5px; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"https://canvas.colorado.edu/courses/123249/files/81499492/download?download_frd=1\"><span role=\"presentation\"><svg viewBox=\"0 0 1920 1920\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" style=\"width:1em; height:1em; vertical-align:middle; fill:currentColor\">\n    <path d=\"m1807.093 1482.477 79.736 79.963-355.313 355.312H355.346L.035 1562.44l79.85-79.963 322.22 322.334H1484.76l322.334-322.334ZM997.677-.033v1167.02l355.313-355.313 79.962 79.85-491.858 491.633L449.46 891.524l79.962-79.85 355.313 355.313V-.033h112.941Z\" fill-rule=\"evenodd\"></path>\n</svg>\n</span><span class=\"screenreader-only\">Download Notebook_Sample_1.ipynb</span></a></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><a class=\"instructure_file_link inline_disabled\" title=\"Notebook_Sample_2.ipynb\" href=\"https://canvas.colorado.edu/courses/123249/files/81499495?wrap=1\" target=\"_blank\" data-canvas-previewable=\"false\" data-api-endpoint=\"https://canvas.colorado.edu/api/v1/courses/123249/files/81499495\" data-api-returntype=\"File\"></a></span><span class=\"instructure_file_holder link_holder instructure_file_link_holder\"><a class=\"inline_disabled\" title=\"Notebook_Sample_2.ipynb\" href=\"https://canvas.colorado.edu/courses/123249/files/81499495?wrap=1\" target=\"_blank\" data-canvas-previewable=\"false\" data-api-endpoint=\"https://canvas.colorado.edu/api/v1/courses/123249/files/81499495\" data-api-returntype=\"File\">Notebook_Sample_2.ipynb</a><a class=\"file_download_btn\" role=\"button\" download=\"\" style=\"margin-inline-start: 5px; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"https://canvas.colorado.edu/courses/123249/files/81499495/download?download_frd=1\"><span role=\"presentation\"><svg viewBox=\"0 0 1920 1920\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" style=\"width:1em; height:1em; vertical-align:middle; fill:currentColor\">\n    <path d=\"m1807.093 1482.477 79.736 79.963-355.313 355.312H355.346L.035 1562.44l79.85-79.963 322.22 322.334H1484.76l322.334-322.334ZM997.677-.033v1167.02l355.313-355.313 79.962 79.85-491.858 491.633L449.46 891.524l79.962-79.85 355.313 355.313V-.033h112.941Z\" fill-rule=\"evenodd\"></path>\n</svg>\n</span><span class=\"screenreader-only\">Download Notebook_Sample_2.ipynb</span></a></span></p>\n<p>Both notebooks use the following dataset:</p>\n<p><span class=\"instructure_file_holder link_holder instructure_file_link_holder\"><a class=\"inline_disabled preview_in_overlay\" title=\"python_data.xlsx\" href=\"https://canvas.colorado.edu/courses/123249/files/81499506?wrap=1\" target=\"_blank\" data-canvas-previewable=\"false\" data-api-endpoint=\"https://canvas.colorado.edu/api/v1/courses/123249/files/81499506\" data-api-returntype=\"File\">python_data.xlsx</a><a class=\"file_download_btn\" role=\"button\" download=\"\" style=\"margin-inline-start: 5px; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"https://canvas.colorado.edu/courses/123249/files/81499506/download?download_frd=1\"><span role=\"presentation\"><svg viewBox=\"0 0 1920 1920\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" style=\"width:1em; height:1em; vertical-align:middle; fill:currentColor\">\n    <path d=\"m1807.093 1482.477 79.736 79.963-355.313 355.312H355.346L.035 1562.44l79.85-79.963 322.22 322.334H1484.76l322.334-322.334ZM997.677-.033v1167.02l355.313-355.313 79.962 79.85-491.858 491.633L449.46 891.524l79.962-79.85 355.313 355.313V-.033h112.941Z\" fill-rule=\"evenodd\"></path>\n</svg>\n</span><span class=\"screenreader-only\">Download python_data.xlsx</span></a></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Before you run either notebook, make sure to load the data, python_data.xlsx, into the folder Content. This can be done by simply clicking on the the Folder Icon on the left menu, and then click on the Upload icon within the Folder.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>If you'd like to challenge yourself with a project in Python, here it is:</p>\n<p>Python Project: Develop a Momentum Trading Signal</p>\n<p><span class=\"instructure_file_holder link_holder instructure_file_link_holder\"><a class=\"inline_disabled preview_in_overlay\" title=\"Project.pdf\" href=\"https://canvas.colorado.edu/courses/123249/files/81563184?wrap=1\" target=\"_blank\" data-canvas-previewable=\"false\" data-api-endpoint=\"https://canvas.colorado.edu/api/v1/courses/123249/files/81563184\" data-api-returntype=\"File\">Project.pdf</a><a class=\"file_download_btn\" role=\"button\" download=\"\" style=\"margin-inline-start: 5px; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"https://canvas.colorado.edu/courses/123249/files/81563184/download?download_frd=1\"><span role=\"presentation\"><svg viewBox=\"0 0 1920 1920\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" style=\"width:1em; height:1em; vertical-align:middle; fill:currentColor\">\n    <path d=\"m1807.093 1482.477 79.736 79.963-355.313 355.312H355.346L.035 1562.44l79.85-79.963 322.22 322.334H1484.76l322.334-322.334ZM997.677-.033v1167.02l355.313-355.313 79.962 79.85-491.858 491.633L449.46 891.524l79.962-79.85 355.313 355.313V-.033h112.941Z\" fill-rule=\"evenodd\"></path>\n</svg>\n</span><span class=\"screenreader-only\">Download Project.pdf</span></a></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"instructure_file_holder link_holder instructure_file_link_holder\"><a class=\"inline_disabled preview_in_overlay\" title=\"Project Data .xlsx\" href=\"https://canvas.colorado.edu/courses/123249/files/81563190?wrap=1\" target=\"_blank\" data-canvas-previewable=\"false\" data-api-endpoint=\"https://canvas.colorado.edu/api/v1/courses/123249/files/81563190\" data-api-returntype=\"File\">Project Data .xlsx</a><a class=\"file_download_btn\" role=\"button\" download=\"\" style=\"margin-inline-start: 5px; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"https://canvas.colorado.edu/courses/123249/files/81563190/download?download_frd=1\"><span role=\"presentation\"><svg viewBox=\"0 0 1920 1920\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" style=\"width:1em; height:1em; vertical-align:middle; fill:currentColor\">\n    <path d=\"m1807.093 1482.477 79.736 79.963-355.313 355.312H355.346L.035 1562.44l79.85-79.963 322.22 322.334H1484.76l322.334-322.334ZM997.677-.033v1167.02l355.313-355.313 79.962 79.85-491.858 491.633L449.46 891.524l79.962-79.85 355.313 355.313V-.033h112.941Z\" fill-rule=\"evenodd\"></path>\n</svg>\n</span><span class=\"screenreader-only\">Download Project Data .xlsx</span></a></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n  \n  \n<div id=\"assign-to-mount-point\"></div>\n<div id=\"choose-editor-mount-point\"></div>",
	"contentText": "Intro to Python for Finance (Optional)\n  \n  \n  \n    If you are interested in learning Python as used in Finance, here are some materials to get you started. This is completely optional (no impact on your class grade), so feel free to disregard if you are not interested.\n \nPython is the language of machine learning models that have become increasingly popular in the last few years. These include artificial intelligence models such as those developed by Open AI (Chat GPT) and Google (Gemini). These models are also beginning to  make inroads into finance as well.\n \nBelow are some materials to get you started on your journey to apply Python in finance.\n \nSet Up\nWe will use Google's Colab environment that was designed specifically for Python projects. All Python projects are coded in Jupyter notebooks. To get on Google's Colab, simply go to: colab.google\n    \n\nLinks to an external site. and click on Open Colab.\n \nSamples of Jupyter Notebooks\nTo get started here are two Jupyter Notebooks that you can load into Colab:\nNotebook_Sample_1.ipynb\n    \n\nDownload Notebook_Sample_1.ipynb\nNotebook_Sample_2.ipynb\n    \n\nDownload Notebook_Sample_2.ipynb\nBoth notebooks use the following dataset:\npython_data.xlsx\n    \n\nDownload python_data.xlsx\n \nBefore you run either notebook, make sure to load the data, python_data.xlsx, into the folder Content. This can be done by simply clicking on the the Folder Icon on the left menu, and then click on the Upload icon within the Folder.\n \nIf you'd like to challenge yourself with a project in Python, here it is:\nPython Project: Develop a Momentum Trading Signal\nProject.pdf\n    \n\nDownload Project.pdf\nProject Data .xlsx\n    \n\nDownload Project Data .xlsx\n \n \n  \n  \n\n",
